PK Shootout

by: Jordan Luo

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I decided to make this game, because I love soccer. I wanted to make a soccer game, because it sounded fun, entertaining, and spent way too long trying to find an idea . In the end I choose to make a soccer game partly because I couldn't think of anything else, sounded fun and not too easy but not too hard . I didn't want to make any other game because a shooting game would probably be too similar to league invaders . Also I couldn't think of anything else .

2. What I Learned

I learned that many people get confused if there is too much going on with too many words. I gave a time limit and they got confused and ran out of that time limit . Also people don't read the directions, at all. I got a lot of feedback to fix glitches, accidental errors, and more time requests. This led me to change the small glitches, and add more time, to have my player have a better experience .

3. Architecture of My Game

I have many different parts of my game including shooting, timer, saving, etc . The shooting makes it so that you can pick where you score, which makes it more fun for the user . The saving and the timer part, make it harder for the user to score . In my game, I have 8 classes in which my game panel does most of the working . Some other classes are there to control specific parts of my game, like the keeper or ball . When they work together, they can put together a game .

4. Technical Implementation

I used 2 timers, one for action preformed, and one for the players shooting timer . The buttons were to pick where you shoot, and were in the button panel class . The aspect in my game i'm , most proud of is the whole game . I didn't have a favorite part, because i'm just proud of all the aspects . I like the way that you can choose where you shoot and the ball goes there . I first had to make a one shot shootout to see if it worked, which took most of my time . Then I had to repeat the PKs, which took a lot of time too .

5. Most Challenging Part

The hardest part of this game was repeating the PK . It took a long time because i had to reset every variable I every used . I had to find every error and change it . It was mostly finding what wrong and fixing it, then reseting another variable . I had so many problems that came up, trying to reset some simple variables . I also had to reset a lot of my code for it to work .

6. Future Fixes and Updates

In the future I would maybe make a 2 player game, where one person could control the keeper . Also I would make it so the keeper could only cover 1 of the 6 possibilities . The only reason why i didn't do that yet is because it would make it too hard on the keeper to save 1 out of 6 places . Also I didn't know what I would do with the scoring, so i haven't done it yet .
